# Docker build context ignore for the web-ui image.
#
# The image is built with `web-ui/` as the context (docker build ... web-ui/),
# so Docker reads THIS file, not the repo-root .dockerignore. Without it, a
# host-built node_modules (wrong platform / stale) would be copied by `COPY . .`
# and shadow the fresh `npm ci` layer, breaking `npm run build`
# (e.g. "Cannot find module '../lib/tsc.js'").
node_modules
dist
.env
*.log
.DS_Store
npm-debug.log*
